error: `send` cannot be combined with an async closure lifted this way: proving the closure's own returned future is `Send` requires naming `AsyncFnMut::CallRefFuture`, which is `#[unstable(feature = "async_fn_traits")]` on stable Rust. Two ways around it: (1) write a plain (non-`async`) closure instead — it reaches every tier, including `send`; or (2) hand-write an `async fn` and lift it with `#[proxima::piped(send)]`, whose `Send`-ness the compiler checks directly against the concrete generated state machine.
